    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "You're basically looking for the file configuring the autocomplete. (My guess would be that there should be something like `autocomplete.js`)\r\nIn this file, there will be the main call to the library:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nautocomplete('xxx', { hint: false }, ...)\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou'll need to add the `debug` and `appendTo` parameter to it, like so:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nautocomplete('xxx', {\r\n  hint: false,\r\n  debug: true,\r\n  appendTo: '.waikiki-search > .search-content'\r\n}, ...)\r\n```",
    "created_at": "2018-07-19T14:41:36Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3036#issuecomment-406300583",
